	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Why not DE?</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Apr 1st 6:33 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I have been playing EQ for almost a year now. I created myself a Dark Elf mage as my first shot at playing a pure caster. So far I have had no problems. the FP militia guards do not love me but they dont attack me either. You can sell to the shady swashbuckler in the tunnel and EC and WC offers a decent supply of wisps when you reach that lv. From reading some of the posts I have to ask this question, Why not a dark elf? You have great starting int, the choice of 3 newbie zones in which to hunt (Nek, EC, West FP) the ability to hide, and the best vision in the game (so you dont have to waste mana summoning a cold stone for yourself). Plus it is easier to raise faction with the light races than it is with the dark. <br>Beware the Demon of Fizzle, dreaded stealer of mana and bane to all who cast everywhere</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
